      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord): send multiple attachments per message",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nDiscord multi-attachment delivery was incomplete across three real paths:\n\n- public Discord action surfaces accepted only scalar `mediaUrl`/`media` values and dropped `mediaUrls` arrays before they reached `sendMessageDiscord`;\n- overflow attachment sends could retry the entire high-level delivery boundary, risking replay of already-sent batches if a later 10-file chunk failed;\n- reply fanout for `replyToMode: \"first\"` was resolved before the multi-attachment send boundary, so the single-use reply could be consumed before the first actual Discord POST or applied inconsistently across overflow batches.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nDiscord allows up to 10 files per message, so OpenClaw has to split larger `mediaUrls` arrays while keeping each actual REST POST independent. This patch keeps plural `mediaUrls` intact through the public action/runtime layers, passes a lazy `replyTo` resolver into multi-media sends so the low-level POST loop consumes it per batch, and removes the high-level retry wrapper around multi-batch deliveries so the existing Discord request retry handles only the failed POST.\n\nSingle-media, component fallback, and voice paths keep the previous string `replyTo` behavior. Voice sends now reject more than one media reference because Discord voice delivery is one file per message.\n\n## User Impact\nUsers can send galleries through Discord with `mediaUrls` from both `sendMessage` and legacy `send` actions. Up to 10 attachments are sent in one Discord message; larger arrays are split into follow-up messages without losing the first reply reference.\n\nIf a transient Discord error happens on an overflow batch, OpenClaw retries that failed batch without reposting the earlier successful attachment batch. Reply modes such as `first` apply to the first real Discord message only, preserving thread context without duplicate reply references.\n\n## Evidence\nHead commit: `1bb1e539cbbbe459967c55c374e0a5c03d12284e`.\n\nLocal targeted behavior proof:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/discord/src/send.sends-basic-channel-messages.test.ts extensions/discord/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/discord/src/actions/runtime.test.ts extensions/discord/src/actions/handle-action.test.ts` -> 4 files passed, 211 tests passed.\n- `pnpm oxfmt --check extensions/discord/src/send.shared.ts extensions/discord/src/send.outbound.ts extensions/discord/src/outbound-payload.ts extensions/discord/src/actions/runtime.messaging.send.ts extensions/discord/src/actions/handle-action.ts extensions/discord/src/send.sends-basic-channel-messages.test.ts extensions/discord/src/outbound-adapter.test.ts extensions/discord/src/actions/runtime.test.ts extensions/discord/src/actions/handle-action.test.ts` -> all 9 touched files formatted.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` -> passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions` -> passed.\n- `git diff --check` -> no whitespace errors.\n\nBehavior cases covered by the tests:\n\n- public `sendMessage` forwards `mediaUrls` arrays into `sendMessageDiscord` and clears scalar `mediaUrl` when plural media is provided;\n- legacy `send` maps `mediaUrls` arrays into the Discord send action;\n- 11 attachments split into 10-file and 1-file Discord POSTs;\n- `replyToMode: \"first\"` adds `message_reference` to the first overflow POST and not the second;\n- a transient failure on the second overflow batch retries only that failed batch and does not replay the first successful batch;\n- plain `mediaUrls` outbound delivery no longer retries the entire send boundary after `sendMessageDiscord` fails.",
        "branch": "codex/discord-max-file-attachments",
        "head_sha": "1bb1e539cbbbe459967c55c374e0a5c03d12284e",
